## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Code Puppy Elixir Control Plane — VM flags
##
## Tuned for an M4 MacBook Air (10 cores: 4P + 6E, 16 GB RAM, fanless).
## These are HARD CAPS — ERL_FLAGS env var, if set, will be appended.
##
## Override any line at runtime via `ERL_FLAGS="+P 262144"` etc.
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Process / port caps — protect a 16 GB laptop from runaway fanout.
## Default BEAM is +P 1048576, +Q 65536. Code Puppy's real working set
## is a few thousand procs, so we cap an order of magnitude lower.
+P 131072
+Q 16384

## Scheduler tuning: leave 2 cores for macOS + REPL/UI.
+S 8:8

## Dirty-CPU schedulers for parsing / hashing (Parsing.Parser, xxhash).
+SDcpu 4:4

## Dirty-IO schedulers for SQLite + file scans.
+SDio 4

## Disable scheduler busy-wait: huge battery + thermal win on fanless Macs.
## Idle schedulers will sleep instead of spinning.
+sbwt none
+sbwtdcpu none
+sbwtdio none

## Lower wakeup threshold so we don't wake too many schedulers at once.
+swt low

## Allocator: address-order best-fit works well for long-lived servers.
+MBas aobf
+MHas aobf

## Max mmap carriers — keeps RSS more predictable.
+MMmcs 30

## Crash dump quiet mode — don't dump 100 MB on every crash in dev.
-env ERL_CRASH_DUMP_SECONDS 0
